## Description
The&nbsp;**Sign Documents** task allows to sign documents with the configured signing profile. The profile will be used to create a specific type of signature (CAdES, XAdES, or PAdES).

> Important

B2G invoices must always be signed, but it is possible to not sign B2B invoices in an Electronic Invoicing workflow.

> Note for internal users

For a detailed technical reference, see: [.bp3/odp3.component-fixture.sign-documents](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=145604785).

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the&nbsp;**Alias**&nbsp;field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the&nbsp;**Signing profile** field, enter the profile code provided by the R&amp;D team.

> Note for internal users

To request a signing profile on DP3, open an Access Management ticket providing the information obtained creating a signing 

profile in the Aruba ASB System.

## Input
The tasks expects the files to be signed as input.&nbsp;

Depending on the provided profile, different signature types can be used for different file types, as detailed in the following table:

Signature type

Possible configuration

Input file type

Notes

**CAdES**

- DETACHED

- *ENVELOPING (not available yet)*

Any document extension

The CAdES signature is applied by the Aruba server.

**XAdES**

- ENVELOPED

- ENVELOPING

- *DETACHED (not available yet)*

XML

The XAdES signature is applied by the Aruba server.

**PAdES**

- ENVELOPING

PDF

The PAdES signature is applied by the Aruba server.

**CERTIFICATE**

Not yet available

Any document extension

The certificate signature is applied by Open SSL with the certificate saved on DP3.

## Output
The task will return the signed documents:

Signature type

Output file type

Notes

**CAdES**

P7M

The system appends the *.p7m* extention to the signed documents (for example, *Filetest.doc* will became *Filetest.doc.p7m*).

**XAdES**

XML

The name of the signed output documents is unchanged.

**PAdES**

PDF

The name of the signed output documents is unchanged.
